+  <h2 id="def_main">Main</h2>
+
+  <div>
+    Pour organiser les &eacute;l&eacute;ments dans un script ou un programme ocaml,
+    il est recommand&eacute; de proc&eacute;der comme suit.
+    Placer l'ensemble des fonctions au d&eacute;but du programme, suivit &agrave;
+    la fin du point d'entr&eacute;e, o&ugrave; l'ex&eacute;cution du programme commencera.
+    (si une fonction est d&eacute;finie mais sans être appel&eacute;e, elle ne
+    r&eacute;alisera rien).
+  </div>
+
+  <div>
+    En C, le point d'entrée est la fonction 'main', en ocaml on place
+    un 'let' suivit d'un 'unit', comme dans cet exemple&nbsp;:
+  </div>
+
+<pre>
+<span class="Stat">let</span> fib n <span class="Stat">=</span>
+  <span class="Stat">let</span> <span class="Stat">rec</span> aux a b acc <span class="Stat">=</span>
+    <span class="Stat">if</span> a &gt; n <span class="Stat">then</span> <span class="Stat">(</span><span class="Mod">List</span>.rev acc<span class="Stat">)</span>
+    <span class="Stat">else</span> aux b <span class="Stat">(</span>a+b<span class="Stat">)</span> <span class="Stat">(</span>a::acc<span class="Stat">)</span>
+  <span class="Stat">in</span>
+  aux <span class="Const">0</span> <span class="Const">1</span> <span class="Const">[]</span>
+
+<span class="Stat">let</span> <span class="Const">()</span> <span class="Stat">=</span>
+  <span class="Stat">let</span> n <span class="Stat">=</span> int_of_string <span class="Mod">Sys</span>.argv.<span class="Stat">(</span><span class="Const">1</span><span class="Stat">)</span> <span class="Stat">in</span>
+  <span class="Stat">let</span> li <span class="Stat">=</span> fib n <span class="Stat">in</span>
+  <span class="Stat">let</span> s <span class="Stat">=</span> <span class="Mod">String</span>.concat <span class="Const">&quot; &quot;</span> <span class="Stat">(</span><span class="Mod">List</span>.map string_of_int li<span class="Stat">)</span> <span class="Stat">in</span>
+  print_endline s<span class="Stat">;</span>
+<span class="Stat">;;</span>
+</pre>
+
+  <div>
+    Ce petit programme affiche la suite de Fibonacci, jusqu'&agrave; un certain nombre
+    pass&eacute; en param&egrave;tre au programme par la ligne de commande&nbsp;:
